# Environment Files — Do Not Modify

**Never delete, overwrite, or replace `.env.local`, `.env`, or any `.env*` file.**

These files contain secrets (API keys, tokens, passwords) that are:
- Not in version control (gitignored)
- Unique to each developer or deployment
- Irrecoverable if lost

## What NOT to do

- ❌ Delete `.env.local` or other env files
- ❌ Overwrite env files with new content (Write tool)
- ❌ Create env files that replace existing ones without explicit user confirmation
- ❌ Assume env files are empty or disposable

## What TO do

- ✅ Only add or update env files if the user explicitly pastes or provides the exact content
- ✅ Use `.env.example` for documentation (placeholder values only, no secrets)
- ✅ If suggesting env vars, tell the user to add them manually to their `.env.local`
- ✅ When in doubt, ask the user to make env changes themselves
